        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 15 at 1:36AM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 135 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles southwest of Geyser, or 19 miles west of Stanford, moving
northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Stanford and Windham.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
